      "releaseNotes": {
        "releaseNotesTooltip": "<div><span class=\"tooltip-title\">What's new in Holoscan 4.2:</span><ul><li>GPU-resident graph execution now supports directed acyclic graphs of operators.</li><li>DEBUG logging enables device-side diagnostics during GPU-resident graph runs.</li><li>The installed SDK includes MatX CMake configuration for downstream integration.</li><li>Updates GXF 5.6, CUDA 13.2, major libraries, and CUDA 13 containers to align with Production Branch 6.</li><li>RMM upgrades introduce API changes that may affect custom GPU memory pool code.</li><li>A new benchmark measures operator performance under `SCHED_DEADLINE` scheduling with background load.</li></ul><a href=\"https://github.com/nvidia-holoscan/holoscan-sdk/releases/tag/v4.2.0#release-notes\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"tooltip-link\">Open Release Notes</a></div>",
        "releaseNotesURL": "https://github.com/nvidia-holoscan/holoscan-sdk/releases/tag/v4.2.0#release-notes",
        "releaseNotesDownload": false
      },
      "releaseMessage": "Holoscan is a domain-agnostic AI computing platform that delivers the accelerated, full-stack infrastructure required for scalable, software-defined, and real-time processing of streaming data running at the edge or in the cloud.",
